{
  "local_port": 60380,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I write a good recommendation for an internship?",
  "response": "Writing a strong recommendation for an internship requires you to highlight the candidate's skills, experiences, and qualities in a way that underscores their suitability for the position. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to crafting an effective recommendation:\n\n1. **Start with a Formal Introduction:**\n   - Use a formal greeting, addressing the specific person (or committee) if you know their name.\n   - Introduce yourself briefly and state your relationship with the candidate (e.g., professor, supervisor).\n   - Mention how long and in what capacity you have known them.\n\n2. **State the Purpose:**\n   - Clearly state that you are recommending the candidate for the specific internship position.\n\n3. **Highlight Key Qualifications:**\n   - Mention specific skills and attributes relevant to the internship.\n   - Provide examples of their achievements or experiences that demonstrate these qualifications.\n\n4. **Include Personal Attributes:**\n   - Discuss the candidate\u2019s personal qualities, such as work ethic, reliability, teamwork, and initiative.\n   - Use anecdotes or specific examples to illustrate these traits.\n\n5. **Relate to the Internship:**\n   - Explain why the candidate\u2019s skills and experiences make them a good fit for this particular internship.\n   - Highlight any unique contributions they could make to the organization.\n\n6. **Conclude with a Strong Endorsement:**\n   - Reiterate your strong recommendation for the candidate.\n   - Offer to provide further information if needed.\n\n7. **Close Formally:**\n   - Use a formal sign-off (e.g., Sincerely, Respectfully).\n   - Include your name, position, and contact information.\n\n**Example:**\n\n[Your Name]  \n[Your Position/Title]  \n[Your Company/Organization]  \n[Your Contact Information]  \n[Date]\n\n[Recipient's Name]  \n[Company/Organization Name]  \n[Company Address]  \n\nDear [Recipient's Name or Hiring Committee],\n\nI am writing to wholeheartedly recommend [Candidate's Name] for the internship position at [Company/Organization Name]. I have had the pleasure of working with [Candidate\u2019s Name] for [Length of Time] as [Your Relation or Position], and have been continually impressed by their dedication, skill, and contribution.\n\n[Candidate\u2019s Name] has consistently demonstrated a strong aptitude in [relevant skill or field], exemplified by [specific example or achievement]. During their time in my class/under my supervision, [they] successfully [describe a relevant project or task], illustrating both technical knowledge and creative problem-solving abilities.\n\nBeyond technical skills, [Candidate\u2019s Name] possesses exceptional personal qualities that make them an asset to any team. [Describe personal attributes such as leadership, communication skills, etc., with examples]. One instance that stood out was when [provide another specific example], exemplifying their commitment and teamwork skills.\n\nGiven their profound skills and reliable work ethic, I am confident that [Candidate\u2019s Name] will make a significant contribution to [Company/Organization Name]. I highly recommend them for this internship without reservation. Please feel free to contact me at [Your Phone Number] or [Your Email Address] for any further inquiries.\n\nThank you for considering this application.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]  \n[Your Position]  \n[Your Organization]  \n\nKeep the recommendation tailored and focused, always providing evidence or examples for the attributes you discuss to make the endorsement powerful and credible.",
